The paper introduces a new family of distributions and a reparameterization trick that can be used in optimization of large scale stochastic computation graphs. This is a topic that is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), neural networks (cs.NE), computer vision (cs.CV), and natural language processing (cs.CL). However, given the focus on optimization and neural networks, cs.LG and cs.AI are the most likely sub-categories, followed by cs.NE, cs.CV, and cs.CL.
